<div id="review_92928031" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/92928031" />
    <a title="Jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica"><img alt="Jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1572125481p2/3283298.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/92928031?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica" href="/user/show/3283298-jessica">Jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3283298-jessica?shelf=16-chick-lit">16-chick-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer92928031" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1191739821196413932">Hmm, can’t say that I’m very fond of this one. I thought the whole plot was really lame. No twists and turns, no dramatic events or anything like that. While reading I kept thinking “this can’t be it, something must happen soon” and I was always waiting for the big climax. I was still waiting for it on the last page….<br/>What I found extremely annoying was the style of writing. All this “and then I was like and then she goes” wasn’t my thing at all. What’s wrong with good old “I said and she replied</span>
  <span id="freeText1191739821196413932" style="display:none">Hmm, can’t say that I’m very fond of this one. I thought the whole plot was really lame. No twists and turns, no dramatic events or anything like that. While reading I kept thinking “this can’t be it, something must happen soon” and I was always waiting for the big climax. I was still waiting for it on the last page….<br />What I found extremely annoying was the style of writing. All this “and then I was like and then she goes” wasn’t my thing at all. What’s wrong with good old “I said and she replied”? Whenever I read these kind of books (High School love stories) I keep comparing them to my favorite book in this category: Perfect Chemistry. So far, I haven’t found a book that came even remotely close to PC. When It Happens didn’t accomplish this task either.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1191739821196413932" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


